FBIS3-36428 "drsov025_h_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 Moldova Electoral Commission Rejects Idea of Poll AU0402134694 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 1100 GMT 4 Feb 94 AU0402134694 Bucharest Radio Romania Network Language: Romanian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Central Electoral Commission of the Republic of Moldova has rejected the proposal put forward by the president and by the presidium of the Moldovan Parliament to organize simultaneously with the parliamentary elections on 27 February a sociological poll in order to confirm the independence of the Republic of Moldova, Chisinau Television reports. The Commission justified this decision by saying that it is not entitled to carry out such polls because the only duty of the commission is to organize parliamentary elections.
